Package com.cafean.client.values.components

Class CReal_E

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.values.components.AbstractValue
      • com.cafean.client.values.components.AbstractCReal
        • com.cafean.client.values.components.CReal_E
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloneableBlock, Checkable, ComponentElement, ModelElement, java.awt.datatransfer.Transferable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    public abstract class CReal_E
extends AbstractCReal
    This class provides a replacement for Real (CReal is shorthand for CAFEAN Real). Of particular noet: this element is a proper ComponentElement. This allows it to store a foreign-key reference to a user-defined real instead of encoding model and component idents within the value field.

    Any method which returns a CReal attempts to instantiate a new instance of the appropriate type; the calling object determines the returned type. For example, calling multiply(CReal) on a Length a and a Width b with the call a.multiply(b) returns a new Length object (even though an extension called Area may exist, which would be more appropriate).

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object o)
        Two CReals are considered equal if one of the following is true:
        • they refer to the same SharedReal
        • neither has a valid reference, and both share a common value (two reals with NaN values are considered equal, even though NaN == NaN returns false).
        Overrides:
        equals in class AbstractCReal
        Parameters:
        o - the Object to be used for comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the blocks are equivalent, else false.

      • readArray

        public static CReal_E[] readArray​(PibFile pibFile,
                                  CReal_E base)
        Read an array of the CReal data blocks from a file. The method signature states that a CReal array is returned (which is technically true), but the array is actually of the type passed in by the base argument, making casts to that type's array class safe.
        Parameters:
        pibFile - An open PIB file containing a random access file with the file pointer located at the start of a CReal block.
        base - an instance of the CReal extension used as a basis for creating elements of the array
        Returns:
        The array or null on failure.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if base is null
